title: chaosdukemon
body:
A Dark Knight Digimon. ChaosDukemon is a [[Dukemon]] whose armor is a dark grey with a purple cape. Its holy lance "Gram" has been replaced with the evil Balmung Spear, and the Gorgon Shield takes the place of Aegis. A theory says that it and [[Megidramon]] are the same being, and that its horrible aura manifests either as a dark knight or a dark dragon depending on the viewer.

ChaosDukemon is referred to as [b]ChaosGallantmon[/b] in English material.

title: blackwargreymon
body: A Dragon Man Digimon. As its name implies, BlackWarGreymon is a [[WarGreymon]] whose body and weapons are entirely black in color, due to it changing into a Virus type. The Brave Shield equipped on its back doesn't show off the Crest of Courage. It hates cowardly and vulgar Digimon, even if they are Virus types as well, and its zero tolerance policy towards foul play has it be feared as the "Jet-black Dragon Warrior".
other_names: ブラックウォーグレイモン

title: metalgreymon
body:
A Cyborg Digimon. MetalGreymon resembles a mechanically enhanced [[Greymon]] with a metallic chest plate and head piece, and a robotic left arm with three huge claws. It also has wings. 

MetalGreymon, much like its predecessor, exists in both Vaccine (orange skin with greenish-blue stripes) and Virus (dark blue skin) forms. For the purposes of this tag, both shall be referred to as one and the same.

title: digitamamon

title: picodevimon
body:

PicoDevimon is referred to as [b]DemiDevimon[/b] in English material.

title: monzaemon
body: A Puppet Digimon. Monzaemon resembles a large, sleepy yellow teddy bear. What drives it is completely unknown. Despite its menacing looks, it is a very benevolent Digimon who hugs others and makes them feel happy.

Scumon is referred to as [b]Sukamon[/b] in English material.

title: arepa-chan
body:
Arepa-chan is an Anime Venezuelan representation of the Arepa, a typical food of this country, consumed in a traditional way; blonde hair represents yellow cheese and aqua eyes represent the eyes colors of the native tribes of the country, is an original character that started on a Facebook page related to the Anime Memes about Venezuela, "Párame Bolas, Senpai", and it is very popular among Venezuelan users who follow that page.

Arepa-chan is a girl given that Venezuela is a feminine name, it is characterized by wearing a loudspeaker, wearing a hat and a jacket with the tricolor colors and the stars of the Venezuelan flag; She does not wear skirts or pants, showing her panties and stockings, a form of Fanservice for the followers of the character.

Venezuelan artists often make FanArts from her and shared by PBS on Facebook.

title: eun_(elsword)
body:
Elsword character. A fox spirit that was sealed inside the a hairpin currently worn by Ara Haan. She saved Ara from Ran during his razing of her village, and continues to be with her in exchange for the promise of freeing her from the seal. In Ara's awakening, Eun's presence takes over and changes Ara's physical appearance to closer match that of Eun's, giving her multiple fox tails, white hair, sharper red eyes, and red whisker marks on her face (and in the Shakti line, fox ears).

In the path of Little Specter > Asura > Shakti, Eun can manifest herself without taking over Ara's body.

title: essex_(warship_girls_r)
body:
The [[personification]] of America's Essex-class Aircraft Carrier [b]USS Essex[/b] (CV-9) in [[Warship Girls R]].

She wears a black suit with white mini-skirt and red breast plate, carries a black flight deck. Her hull number "9" is written on the flight deck and her right shoulder in white. She usually has an expressionless face with flat gaze, and a [[twintails]] hair style.
She is always seen accompanied by a little bald eagle [[Bell McCamp (warship girls r)|Bell McCamp]]. Being a quite and shy character, she has very little to say, and usually lets Bell does all the talking.

title: bell_mccamp_(warship_girls_r)
body:
A [[bald eagle]] accompanying [[Essex (warship girls r)|USS Essex]] in [[Warship Girls R]]. He does most of the talking since Essex is essentially a silent character, having very few spoken lines in-game.

Bell is grumpy and has a rather short temper, often resulting in him yelling commentary here and there.
He is a full-size, realistic bald eagle most of the time, but will turn into an egg-shaped chibi when Essex is critically damaged. 

Quite probably a reference to the bald eagle on the ship's emblem of USS Essex. 

The name "Bell McCamp" is wordplay referring to real-life pilot "David McCampbell":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/David_McCampbell, the Essex Ace pilot who shot down 34 Japanese planes during his service.

title: mig-31
body:
A Russian [[fighter jet]].

Developed as a successor to the [[MiG-25]], the MiG-31 (NATO reporting name: Foxhound) first flew in 1979. Its general appearance is very similar to that of its predecessor: a bulky aircraft with large shoulder-mounted delta wings, rectangular air intake trunks, and sharply swept tailplanes. Differences include the canopy frames, the presence of a second canopy for the dedicated weapon system officer, a small leading edge extension, outward-canted vertical fins and larger engine exhausts.

The MiG-31 is slower than the MiG-25, but is better armed and has improved avionics and maneuverability.

Main armament consists primarily of the R-33/AA-9 'Amos' air-to-air missile and a 23mm cannon. The MiG-31 can also carry other air-to-air missiles and fuel tanks.

This jet fighter is featured in the anime [[Stratos 4]], where a modified version is used by the protagonists.

h4. See also

body:
[b]Shouji[/b] (障子) are a type of [[door]], [[window]], or room divider in traditional [[east asian architecture|Japanese architecture]]. They consist of thin, translucent paper on a wooden lattice frame. The paper is thin enough to let light in, but not to see through.

Shouji can be used as [[sliding doors]] or as windows. Sometimes, shouji panels may include a small glass window to see through.

Shouji are similar to [[fusuma]], another type of sliding paper panel. The difference is that [[fusuma]] are made of thick, opaque paper that doesn't let light through.

title: tv_camera
body:
A large professional high-end video camera used by television studios and other businesses or organizations that need such devices.  Three major types of these are: studio cameras, Electronic News Gathering (ENG) cameras (like those used with field reporters), and Electronic Field Production (EFP) cameras (likes those used to broadcast professional sports). 

Only ENG cameras have the ability to record, making them similar to consumer [[camcorder]]s, although they tend to be much larger, heavier, and have a variety of other differences.  Studio and EFP cameras lack the ability to record anything and are tethered by cables to the other equipment that records and/or transmits the video for broadcasting.

h4. See also

* [[camera]] 
* [[movie camera]] 
* [[video camera]]

title: movie_camera
body:
A camera that captures a rapid succession of pictures onto film.  By playing the film in an appropriate projector, the images can be viewed in rapid succession to produce an animated picture of what was originally viewed by the camera.  

Not to be confused with the [[camcorder]] tag, which is a portable device that is composed of a video camera and video recorder.  These devices use electronic motion picture acquisition, instead taking a rapid sequence of photos to film, and tend to look very different.

title: pink_leotard_(dq)
body:
An item in [[Dragon Quest IV]]. It is a pink [[swimsuit]]/[[leotard]] with an opening at the front and a [[brooch]] above the opening at the cleavage area and below the opening near the crotch area, though sometimes artists omit these brooches. Characters wearing the pink leotard are often drawn with pink [[leg warmers]].

In the subsequent games it was replaced by the [[angel leotard]]; the DQ4 remake for the Playstation has both.

title: symmetra_(overwatch)
body:
[i]"The true enemy of humanity is disorder."[/i]

Real Name: Satya Vaswani
Age: 28
Occupation: Architech
Country: India

A support-class character in [[Overwatch]]. After she was identified as one of the few capable of becoming a light-bending architech, Satya was plucked from extreme poverty and placed in the care of Vishkar's Architech Academy, never to return home. Isolated and lonely in her new life, Satya immersed herself in her education and training. Satya approached hard-light manipulation differently than her peers by weaving her constructs in the motions of the traditional dance of her homeland. Her abilities earned her the moniker "Symmetra".

VA: Anjani Bhimani (English), [[nabatame_hitomi|Hitomi Nabatame]] (Japanese), Carla Castañeda (Latin American Spanish), Silvia Sarmentera (European Spanish), Tulika Srivastava (French)

title: sakata_kintoki_(gintama)
body:
[[Gintama]] character. He has straight and golden hair and also light blue eyes. He wears the opposite color of Gintoki by having white boots, white shirt and pants with blue linings, and a black yukata with golden patterns worn sloppily, draped over his left shoulder like Gintoki.

All is opposite from Gintoki. 

He was built by [[Hiraga Gengai]] by orders of [[Kagura (Gintama)|Kagura]] and [[Shimura Shinpachi]] who were mad at [[Sakata Gintoki|Gintoki]] for leaving them behind. In order for them to keep doing their work they decided to came up with ideas to make the perfect yorozuya substitute leader that would fill in Gintoki's spot when he was absent. 

His seiyuu is [[Nakamura Yuuichi]].

Not to be confused with [[Sakata Gintoki]]. While similarly named to [[Kintarou]], his character is not directly based on him.
